commentTextItems.html: that shall do it for West Indies, Darren Sammy gets under this pitched up delivery and lifts it over the infield, there is deep midwicket, but a single is all West Indies need, and Sammy strolls to the other end with a smile on his face

commentPostTextItems.html: That is all from this game. The series is alive for the final match in Kanpur. It is a day game on Wednesday. Abhishek Purohit signing off till then. Good night.

Darren Sammy is the Man of the Match. Sammy: "I must thank my team-mates for giving me another opportunity. It must have been difficult to do that, seeing how the series has gone for me. Simmons and I communicated well. We backed ourselves to get 90-odd in the last ten overs. Once I am hitting the ball nicely, it was always good for me. Good to contribute in a crucial game."

Dwayne Bravo: "Great team effort. Holder and Rampaul gave us a good start, can't forget young Permaul. Once we got the Indians under 300, we backed ourselves to chase. We planned very well. It was a must-win game for us. We communicated well on the field. The bowlers executed. We fielded well. Bowling to MS, the best player in the world, is always difficult. Well done to young Powell, Simmons and Darren Sammy. Myself getting out at a crucial time. Our aim was for one of the top five batters to bat through the innings. We had four half-centuries today, so that was good."

MS Dhoni: "There was a lot of dew, was difficult for bowlers to even grip the ball, let along putting it in right areas. Toss was crucial. To take it to the last over was a superb bowling effort. The spinners did really well. When we went into bowl, there was plenty of dew, and it kept getting worse. It was very difficult to score runs and rotate strike. We saw that when they batted as well. If there was no dew, 289 was 400-odd on this pitch with so much turn and bounce."

Not often can you accuse him of not throwing his wicket away, but for once, Darren Sammy has done exactly the same. He came in at 185 for 5. There was extra responsibility as West Indies were playing an extra bowler. They needed 22 more when Simmons fell but Sammy wasn't going to give it away tonight. This is as sensible a finishing innings as you'll ever see, and he's still managed a strike-rate of 140. He's led West Indies to their fourth-highest successful chase

Catches galore going down this game. West Indies put down a couple, but India outdid them by dropping at least five chances, including Darren Bravo thrice in four balls. Yuvraj put down Simmons on 43. West Indies were 215 for 5 then.

Lendl Simmons [on what he and Sammy were thinking]: "Just knock it around, keep rotating the strike, build a partnership, bat till the end. Sammy batted well. We stuck to our gameplan and executed it well." Simmons adds it was difficult to bowl. The ball was changed twice when West Indies batted, there was so much dew around.
Kamal: "I'm looking for the guy who sent that feedback saying Sammy's been in the team only to take good catches. #MotherOfJinxes"

commentPreTextItems.html: All men saving the single in the circle

commentTextItems.html: Mohit goes up in appeal for lbw, this cut in and hit him too high, Sammy and Permaul kept their cool to sneak in the leg bye as the ball rolls square on the off side

commentPreTextItems.html: Second bat change for Sammy. Mohit Sharma will bowl the last over

commentTextItems.html: Sammy was winding up, but he saw this bowled slow, and reined himself in to tap it into the off side for a single

Sammy goes for glory off the short ball and swipes hard, it flies in the air, Yuvraj at midwicket puts in a theatrical dive, but it eludes him, there is a man in the deep though, and Sammy keeps strike for the last over

flicked elegantly in the air off the pad and Holder comes back for a couple
that should do it, Sammy receives another high full toss and smashes it in the same region, this time it clears deep midwicket past the desperate, futile attempt from the fielder
Sammy is sealing this for West Indies, a full toss around off stump, he swings it right between deep midwicket and long on
pushed down to long off for a single
this drive hits the gap between short third man and backward point, and Holder releases a lot of pressure with this boundary
that is another chance, albeit a tough one, there is a sound as the ball passes Holder's bat on the attempted drive, but Dhoni is standing up, and this one does no stick
a low full toss driven wide of long off, but they'll get only a single, and that brings up a sensible, vital half-century for the West Indies Test captain

headshotImage.caption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina c DJ Bravo b Rampaul 23 (24b 2x4 0x6 49m) SR: 95.83

dismissalComment.html: Raina falls by the swipe, Rampaul pitches it up from round the wicket, angles it in to leg stump, Raina swings, and top-edges to extra cover

headshotImage.caption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Holder b Rampaul 99 (100b 9x4 0x6 159m) SR: 99

dismissalComment.html: Kohli is out for 99, it was a bouncer at the head, Kohli pulled, the ball swirled down to fine leg, where the giant Holder dives forward to pluck it very low, then gets up and roars as Kohli stands stunned, they check for the no-ball but Rampaul is alright

headshotImage.caption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ravindra Jadeja b Rampaul 10 (20b 0x4 0x6 27m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: that'll do, Jadeja has looked thoroughly unconvincing, and has his leg stump uprooted, he just stands in the crease and wafts weakly, Rampaul angles the length ball in, past whatever Jadeja was trying, and into the stumps

headshotImage.caption: Johnson Charles player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Johnson Charles player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ravichandran Ashwin c †Charles b Holder 19 (10b 2x4 1x6 18m) SR: 190

dismissalComment.html: he tries a reverse sweep, against a fast bowler, goes down on a knee outside leg stump, but only feathers it through to the keeper

headshotImage.caption: Johnson Charles player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Johnson Charles player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Johnson Charles player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Johnson Charles player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Johnson Charles c & b Kumar 12 (9b 2x4 0x6 10m) SR: 133.33

dismissalComment.html: Bhuvneshwar finds himself in the way of this mistimed swat from Charles, it smacks him in the stomach, he wraps his hands around the ball and sends Charles back, Charles went after this length ball, but it bounced and hit the bat quite high, so that it looped back and took Bhuvneshwar down as well, he's lost his breath but the wicket will help him get it back

headshotImage.caption: Kieran Powell player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kieran Powell player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Kieran Powell player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kieran Powell player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kieran Powell st †Dhoni b Ashwin 59 (70b 7x4 1x6 116m) SR: 84.28

dismissalComment.html: oh dear, what's Powell done, he's walked out in a daze past Ashwin's flighted offbreak, big turn past the bat as he tries to weakly defend, stranded miles down the track, another waste of a wicket, more reward for the disciplined Ashwin

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels c †Dhoni b MM Sharma 8 (10b 2x4 0x6 14m) SR: 80

dismissalComment.html: this is sensational from Dhoni, Mohit is bowling well into the mid-130s, the captain decides to come up, the bowler gets one to move in slightly after pitching on a good length, Samuels goes for another drive, and the thin edge is snapped up low by the captain, who jumps immediately in delight, what a sharp, sharp take

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Darren Bravo c †Dhoni b Ashwin 50 (54b 8x4 0x6 71m) SR: 92.59

dismissalComment.html: the partnership is broken on 100, this time Dhoni holds on to the catch, Bravo tries to cut one too close to the off stump, and it is a healthy edge to the keeper, once again, West Indies have given India an opening, despite the numerous dropped catches, just reward for Ashwin, who has bowled with superb control with a wet ball

dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons lbw b Jadeja 62 (74b 5x4 1x6 116m) SR: 83.78

dismissalComment.html: that's a goner, with the last ball of his spell, Jadeja keeps India alive, this comes in with the angle, Simmons is caught on the crease, misses the whip and is hit low on the pad in front of middle and leg

headshotImage.caption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Bravo c Dhawan b Kumar 18 (26b 2x4 0x6 33m) SR: 69.23

dismissalComment.html: and another West Indies gift falls in India's lap, Bravo had batted quite well till now, he's tried manufacturing a boundary with a pick-up pull on one leg, and has found the man on the deep square leg boundary with precision

dismissalText.commentary: Daren Sammy not out 63 (45b 4x4 4x6 81m) SR: 140

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jason Holder c †Dhoni b Mohammed Shami 7 (5b 1x4 0x6 7m) SR: 140

dismissalComment.html: Holder gives it away with a skip down the track and a swing of the bat, thick edge settles into Dhoni's gloves, quite needless

headshotImage.caption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c sub (AT Rayudu) b Mohammed Shami
dismissalText.commentary: Sunil Narine c sub (AT Rayudu) b Mohammed Shami 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: oh dear, another one throws it away, Narine tries an almighty pull, he is hurried for pace on the short ball, and the top edge ends in square leg's hands, they cross over, and Sammy will be on strike next ball
